values: Hello to all...just me hangin out...reading some old posts...trying to enjoy the break...make some $ at work. got bills to pay you know. The usual I guess. not much to report except we're actually using the computers at work as of the 1st of the year...kinda nice after almost 2 years of promises! ;-)

Hola, Buenas dias! Estoy bien, pero muy cansado. (That means tired right?) Anyway, I'm working on 27 hours straight...no sleep and it's only 1 pm today! Woo Hoo! Yaay for finals! Anyway, next Finals week (Spring) will be my last undergrad finals week...crazy...kinda weird...but I'm working on that. No really, I'm checkin' out grad schools...soon to choose where to apply to.

So yeah, I just learned I got a 74 on my Spanish final...not the grade I wanted, but apparently I still got a B in the class and the teacher thought I was "a really good student" in her email. That's kinda cool. So I'm going to get to move on to my LAST spanish class next semester! I finished my Western Culture Hieritage class 3303 today....last one of three. That was nice to do. Well, I got a final this afternoon to study for...and I'm not sure anyone reads my journal anymore since I rearly post...lol Laterz!

Hey ALL you people,

    I'm going ok. Not sure if it's allergies or a cold...either way I'm trying to get over it. So I'll keep this short and brief so I can go to bed! :-D School's almost over...only about a month left. That's crazy, especially when I realize I've only got one more semester before I graduate and move on to more school...At least it'll be grad school though. But, I'm not sure where I'm going to go. I need to make some decisions...soon. I also need to sit down and study math and all that so I can Retake the GRE and hopefully not bomb it this time...it wasn't horrible...well, ok, the math part was horrible. BUT, I got a respectable grade on my essay...apparently it made sense, but had a some 'errors' in it.

    So, I should be going now. But life is good, busy, but good. Catch you laterz.

Ah yes....staying busy and yet it seems like I'm not doing much sometimes. This is the dilemma I deal with occasionally...(usually when I'm sitting at home or at school, contemplating what school work I should be doing.) Anyway, so I almost had a heart-attack before class today when my classmate asked me if I'd studied for spanish class, something about a test.!. Well, no I had not...I didn't even go to class last Thursday...so I had missed the announcement. BUT, turns out it was just a practice exam and wasn't graded. Which came to my relief. And now, I know what to study for for the real thing this Thursday! Looks like I'll be up late most day's this week. I need a good grade in spanish...since I kinda bombed the first test.

Well, it has definitely been a while since I've posted. I used to post kinda regularly...what happened?
Oh, that's right, LIFE happened, in that I mean school, work, family, friends, IV, etc. etc. Well, quick update(s):
My car is running, not great, still needs lots of work. Definitely a point A point B car now. But I'm worried that might not be the case if I don't get to working on it soon!
School is keeping me busy. I've had at least one test in each of my 4 classes. I've done well, and poorly, on them. Spanish sucked because I didn't really study and then I had a total mental retreival  breakdown and could not remember the endings to one of the tenses...yeah, that's not a good thing.
Work is just as normal as ever, I guess. Although Medicaid just changed (as of 10/01/2005) their policy for those 21 years of age and older...they can now get glasses and exams every 24 months(just in case you were wondering).
Intervarsity has been awesome lately! We just got back from our weekend get-away (The Great Escape). I played with the Worship Team during the weekend and that was a good experience. The speaker, Don Everts, was awesome as well! I'll have to fill in about this some more later.
And Last but by far NOT LEAST, my relationship with Christin is going well....8 months to the day! (yeah, that's 4 months shy of a year... ;-)
Anywayz, I got to run. I'll add more laterz!

I hope Ya'll can see this, If not...let me know :-)

Hey everyone, How's it going? I'm staying busy as usual. Though not so Busy. I haven't posted any of the pics of my car...if I were not at school, I'd do it now, but you'll have to wait some more. ;-) Anyway, so what has everyone been up to? Me lots of stuff.

Ok here's another brief update from before school started. I had summer school all of July, that went well! Considering I missed the ENTIRE first week of it. Yeah, I thought I was dead...dropped, or would be, from the class, missed the Drop with a W date, Missed the Refund withdrawal date, and of course, an entire week(5 2.4 hour days) of class. BUT, I was very blessed and I jumped right in and ended up getting an A, IN SPANISH of all classes!

Well, after that I was free to work full time. Which was nice. I started saving so I could essentially be in a position to pay off my credit card a little way into the semester, even WITH school expenses. BUT, alas, my driving 'crashed' that hope. I think it was God saying 'HEY, STOP BEING A BAD DRIVER!' I can admit it, I haven't been using Good habits lately. Talking and Texting on the phone while driving are a few of the bad habits. Well, in case you're wondering, it is rather difficult to correct for a skid/fish-tail with a phone in your hand. Also, DON'T STEP ON THE BRAKE WHEN YOU BEGIN TO SKID! I knew that...but I wasn't THINKING about what I was doing and did it anyway. SO, I swerved to the right, realized my mistake, steered into the skip (turned the wheels right, WITH ONE HAND) until the wheels got traction again. THEN IT GOT "FUN". My car when from sliding sideways to the right, to an ALMOST entire 360 degrees to the left when the front wheels got traction but I couldn't straighten them out BECAUSE I ONLY HAD ONE HAND ON THE WHEEL. you'd think I'd have been shaken or stirred or something after all the excitement. But NO, I just found myself sitting on the curb thinking, 'DANG, I knew better than that'.

Anyway, just for the fun of it I'm gonna draw my accident out for ya! And then post it for ALL to see. I'm lucky not to have been injured or to have injured anyone else in my carelessness. And I'm very Thankful for that! Thank You God!

Well, Catch you all laterz.

Hello. Man it's been a while since I've posted anything. Well, I've got a few spare minutes between classes here and I figured I'd BRIEF you on all that's happening. So here goes:
1)I'm back at utep for my final two semesters (graduate in May) and doing stuff that graduation entails.
2)I'm officially part of the Servant(Leadership) Team for Intervarsity Christian Fellowship UTEP Chapter. My official title is Treasurer. But as anyone who's done Leadership in IV before knows, there's a lot more to it that just doing your job.
3) Still working, though I've recently gotten a raise and am very happy about that! Only get about 18 hours a week, but hopefully with the raise I'll be able to pay for my gas!
4)Which reminds me, I'm still working, yes fixing, my car after my late afternoon 'slide' down Timberwolf and into the curb. There is much more to that story but that'll have to wait. I'll post pics up soon to show just what I did to my poor car. :-(
5) Last but DEFINITELY NOT LEAST, I'm still very much enjoying spending lots of time with my girlfriend Christin! I Love You! We're doing well. It'll be 7 months that we've been a couple in a few days.
Well, I suppose that's about all I really have time to post. So let that suffice until next time, which hopefully won't be quite so long from now! Laterz peoplez

Hello everyone, hope you're doing well.?. I'm good. Got a lot of studying to do for tomorrows test, but I'm feeling quite confident that I'll get it all done and do well.
    Got an email from Chris today. He and his partners have returned to Nairobi Kenya, where there is running water and electricity, to meet the rest of the team. He's doing good...no illnesses or run-in's with the wildlife...he's still got about 2 weeks before he's home, but it's good to hear he's having fun while spreading God's word!

Once again I've decided to post! :-P lol, anyway. I've been posting much more regularly than normal...and for once, I've decided to make this one readable by all. :-) The last few are for my eyes only....for now anyway. Things have been, well, up and down. But mostly UP. Sunday was a really good day I'd say. Nothing huge to speak of except that my mom, Christin's parents, Christin and I all (total of 5) went to Music Under the Stars. It was a really good evening. If you're ever in El Paso and have the chance to go to teh Chamizal National Memorial for Music Under the Stars....GO!!! Even if it'snot your favorite music...the weather's nice and the park is just really beautiful with the sunset...a genuine, almost, 'small town' feel to it. Very cool!

    So yeah, we did that, Christin and I danced...admittedly, we're not the GREATEST dancers ever. But she did express her wish to take dance lessons to get better and I really think that's a cool idea! (notation...lessons so WE get better...the implication was not solely on her!!) We'll have to look into it. Well, I suppose that that is really the only interesting news from my part of the world...well, new news anyway. Hope you're having a good week and had a good weekend! :-)

So I've finally sat down long enough to write more than two sentences! :-) How is everyone doing? I'm good. Things, though busy (at times) are going well. I'm getting, roughly speaking, a million more hours at work than I was during the school year. Which is a good thing. I had a WHOPPING 54 hours on my last pay check...yeah, so it's not full-time, but a lot more than my school year average of 30.

Anyway, yeah. Been spending lots of time with Christin as well. That's a good thing too! It's hard to describe in words that do justice to a relationship in which things 'just fit', 'make sense', 'work out', or any other phase you like. It really is going well ;-)

I've also been going to several group Bible studies. However, I've decided I'm really going to need to not go to some. I've just got other 'things'/activites I want/need to do. So, now I just got to decide which not to go to. How's that for a twist in life...DECIDING which Bible study NOT to go to.......

Hi there, it's been a while...quite a while actually. Anyway, things are going pretty well. Been rather busy considering it's Summer. But oh well, such is life. Hope all is well with you peoples. More to come...when I have more time to sit an write.

Hola! How is the world treating people? Not great? Ah, yeah...that happens. Anyway, I'm doing well. It's summer time for me...time for makin' money, vacationing (I realize this conflicts with making money), and just getting things done in general. The usual stuff. Hopefully I'll have time to get away a couple of times this summer...Stephanie and Fernando's wedding went well yesterday! I really enjoyed myself at both the service and the reception afterwards. Spent some quality time with Christin. She was even kind enough to dance a few songs with me. And I'm happy she did, Thanks Darling! :-D

Words are funny things. They can be so mean. People use them to state their intentions...some people use them to hide their intentions. Funny things words are. Sometimes they're genuinly meant. Sometimes they're used just to simply be used. There are bad words. There are evil and hateful words. "Sticks and stones may break my bones, but words will never  hurt me" is such a lie. To tell someone they're dumb or ugly can have such a profound effect on a person...especially a loved one...

....and then....it feels so good to tell her she's Beautiful....and mean it

Hey people...have i  mentioned I don't like Finals? I don't...it's early and my paper isn't done. It's my fault, yes, but I still don't like finals. 
Thanks for the love and support! (special thanks to Christin, for being so encouraging, understanding, and supportive!!!)You amaze me :-)

Hello everyone! How's it goin? I'm not doin' too bad. :-D Actually, I'm doing pretty well. School's almost over for the semester. Just two and a half weeks left! Well, one 1/2 weeks plus Finals week. Things outside of school are goning well too. Things in the 'relationship' are going well ;-)

God is truelly an awesome God! This last weekend my brother Chris had a 'fundraiser' for his missions trip to Kenya! (Man it's weird to think of Chris being in Africa!! That's cool!!!) Anyway, Chris had not done any money raising until this weekend. We, our immediate family, served lunch to our church congregation and other family and friends. Chris needed roughly $3,000+ for his trip. That's a LOT of money, mony my family doesn't have to give to him. Well, the people at Zion Evangelical Lutheran (LCMS) responded, BIG! Over $2,000 BIG!!! There is no question that Chris will get the rest of the money he needs to go on this missions trip! Thank you God! Nothing is impossible in you!
